                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A homunculus can't speak, but it is telepathically linked to its creator. It can share information back and forth, including its master's knowledge and everything the homunculus hears. The range of this link is 1,500 feet. The homunculus typically has a similar attitude to its creator and is utterly faithful.</p>\n<p>If the homunculus is destroyed, the master takes @Damage[2d10[mental]] damage. If the master is slain, the homunculus becomes mindless, claims its current location as its lair, and instinctively attacks anyone who comes near.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "ORC",
                    "remaster": true,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "arcane",
                        "mental"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
